vango (anat. and fig.) cheek; vangoza chubby: full cheeked; vangegi, vangosako jowls; 
cheek-pouch (of certain monkeys); vangobarbo whisker(s); vangofrapar, vangbatar to slap, cuff, 
strike (ulu) on the face.

varma (also fig.) warm; varmega hot; varmeta tepid, lukewarm; varmeskar 
to get warm; varmigar to heat, warm; varmig(ad)o heating; varmigilo heating apparatus; 
ped, lit, pladvarmigilo foot-, bed-, plate-warmer. Ant.: kolda.

vendar (tr.) to sell; vendo, vendado sale, selling; vendeyo, venderio shop, store; 
vendanto, vendinto, vendisto dealer, vendor; vendebla vendible, salable, marketable; vendotable 
shop counter; vendkontrato bargain (written). Ant.: komprar.

veneno (also fig.) venom, poison; venena, venenoza venomous, poisonous; (fig.) 
malignant; venenagar (tr.) to poison (ulu); venenizar to put poison on (ulo); 
rat veneno rat poison.

verda (color) green, verdant; verdeso green(ness); verdajo a g. object; verdure; 
(pl., fig.) salad-herbs, pot-herbs; verdigar, verdizar to make, cover with, g.; verdeskar 
to turn g.

verifikar (tr.) to verify (by examination), to confirm; to try, test (weights and measures); 
to audit; to prove (a will); verifik(ad)o verification, examining, auditing; (of wills) probate; 
verifikisto, verifikero verifier, inspector, auditor. Def.: Kontrolar l’exakteso, justeso di kalkulo, di 
mezuro o mezurilo; III-203. Ex.: L’evento verifikas lua predico. Verifikar aserto, signaturo.

vertijar, vertijeskar (intr.) to be dizzy, have a swimming, whirling sensation; (cf. aturdar); 
vertijo vertigo, dizziness, giddiness; vertijanta dizzy (sensation, head); (med.) vertiginous; 
vertijigiva, vertijiganta causing dizziness (heights, etc.).

vespero evening; vesperala evening, vesper (star, prayer, etc.); vespere in the evening; 
vesperfesto, vesperkunveno evening party, soiree; ca vespere this evening; pasar la vespero to 
spend the e.; dicar (od, dezirar) bon vespero (ad ulu): to say good e.

veturo vehicle (serving to transport persons or merchandise, carriage, wagon, conveyance; 
veturirar (od, veturvehar) to go, travel, drive in a v.; veturagar, veturtransportar 
to carry in vehicle (cf. vehigar); veturedo wagonful; quarrota veturo four wheeled v.; 
manu, hom veturo hand-cart; lokac veturo v. for hire, fly.

vidar (tr.) to see; vidigar (ulo da ulu) to cause someone to see 
something; vid(ad)o sight, vision: act of seeing; vidajo what is seen, a sight, a view; 
videyo (locality) viewpoint; vidpunto (mental) viewpoint, point of view; vidala visual; 
videbla visible, apparent (cf. aparanta, semblanta); vidinda worth seeing; vidindajo 
something worth seeing; videnda what ought or must be seen; vidorgano organ of vision; 
mi vidar to catch a glimpse of, see imperfectly; inter vido interview: meeting for conference. 
Ex.: La lasis me vidar nulo, ma lu vidis omno vidinda. Konocar ulu per la vido. Pagebla ye vido. V. exp.: 
vid. regardar.

vildo (wild) game; vildoza full of g.; vildizar to stock with g.: vildchasar, vildkaptar 
to hunt; vildkaptisto, vendisto fowler, sportsman; dealer in g.; vildokarno flesh of g.; 
vildosako g. bag; plum vildo feathered g.; wild fowl.

violacar (tr.) to violate: to infringe, transgress, break a law, one’s oath); 
to ravish, rape (a female); violaco rape; violation; violacante la reguli in violation of the 
rules.

vitro (the material) glass; vitra (made of) g.; vitrala, vitratra glass, vitreous; vitrizar 
to furnish or cover (ulo) with g. (windows, etc.); vitrizisto glazier (cf. glezar); 
vitrigar (tr.), vitreskar (intr.) to vitrify; vitrifar to make g.; 
vitriferio g. works; vitrifisto g. maker; vitrokarelo pane (as of a window); vitrotekto 
g. roof; vitropapero sand-paper; vitroparieto g. partition; vitroplako plate g.; 
vitrachajo, vitraji glass trinkets, g. beads.

vorto (written, printed) word (cf. parolo); vortaro collection of words; vocabulary; 
vortolibro word-book, dictionary; vortope, vortopa verbatim, word for word, literal (translation); 
vortifar to build words; vortif(ad)o word building.

votar (intr.) to vote (either viva voce or by ballot) (por, kontre) (tr.) 
to v. for (ulu); to enact (ulo); vot(ad)o vote, voting; voice, suffrage, ballot; 
votanto, votinto voter; votyuro right to v.; balotvoto vote by (second) ballot; listo voto ballot by list; 
votokonto polling: count of votes; voto per manui show of hands; votado universala universal suffrage; 
votar por lego to vote for a law; votar lego to enact a law.

voyo (tera, fera, mara) way, road; (R.R.) track, route; 
voyeto path(way), footpath; voyego broad road, highway; voyifar to make a road; 
mi voyo (ye) half-way; lakto voyo (astron.) Milky Way; fer voyo railroad; 
kargoletro fervoyala way-bill; voyadministrado administration of public ways; 
voylaboristo road worker.

voyajar (intr.) to travel; (by water) to voyage; voyajeskar to start on a journey; 
voyajo travel(ing); trip (cf. turo); voyajado frequent or continued travel; 
voyajanta; voyajero traveling, traveler, passenger; voyajema; voyajemo (person) fond of t.; itinerant, strolling; 
voyajospensi traveling expenses; vivo voyajo (fig.) life’s journey; 
komerc voyajisto commercial traveler; voyajera kolombo carrier pigeon. Ex.: Voyajar en Azia, 
de London a New York.

vu (pl. vi) you; (for familiar usage cf. tu); vua (pl. via 
or vui) your(s), your own; vua relati your relations; mea esas verda, vua  esas reda mine is green, yours (pl.) are red; ube esas la kamizi? Vui esas en l’armoro  e mei esas en la laveyo where are the shirts? yours are in the press and mine are in the wash; 
prenez elia manteli kun vii take their cloaks with your own (pl.).

vulgara vulgar: used or done by the common run of people, common, popular, unrefined; (N.B. 
for low, coarse sense, cf. grosiera, nepolita, malgusta); (noun form = populo, turbo, plebeyaro); 
vulgareso (quality) vulgarism: commonness, unrefinedness (N.B. not «low» cf. grosierajo); 
vulgarigar to vulgarize: make popular; vulgariganto, vulgarero popularizer; vulgara traduko di Biblo 
vulgar version of the Bible (cf. vulgato); vulgara parolado, opiniono, prejudiki vulgar tongue, 
opinion, prejudices.

yaro year, twelvemonth; yarala yearly, annual; relating to y.; -ala (od, 
unyara) planti annual plants; yarlibro yearbook, annual (cf. 
almanako); singla, omnayara, yare yearly; which takes place every year; 
yardeko decade; yardeka happening every ten years (cf. dekyara); 
yarcento century; miyara twice a year; yarrento annuity; 
cayare, yara this year; ante un yaro one year ago; en yaro mezvalora 
in the average year, one year with another.

yen (conjunction with an interjectional character) (with or without hike, ibe) here is, there is; 
(interj. meaning) look here! behold! lo! yen la volfo here is the wolf; look, the wolf! 
yen (hike) me here I am; yen (ibe) lu there he is; yen me behold, it is I! 
yen lu there he comes; yen pomi, prenez le bona here are apples, take the good ones; 
yen (ke) la treno arivas here comes the train; yen quale la kozi eventis 
this is how things happened; yen me itere here I am again.

yuna young; yunesala juvenile, youthful; yuno, yunulo, yunino a young person; 
yuneso (time) youth; yunaro (collect.) youth; yunesala stroko prank, frolic; 
yunesala aspekto youthfulness (in appearance). Note: The suffix yunid denotes the descendant, offspring of persons: 
Izraelido, Napoleonido. For progeny other than of persons yunyuno is used: 
bovyuno, kavalyuno,  etc. V. exp.: vid. anciena. Ant.: olda.

yuro right (founded on law, property, vested interest) legal-right, -title, -authority; right (moral claim founded on justice, equity); (cf. 
lego, yusteso); yurocienco law (as a science); jurisprudence; yuristo jurist; 
yurizar to entitle, authorize, give the (legal) right to; (cf. darfar); 
yurizita entitled, legitimate, lawful; yurizo authorization; yuriziti (jur.) assigns. 
Ex.: La legi definas la yuri di la homi. La yuro votar esas civitanala yuro. Yuro naturala. 
Yuro defensar su, parolar (pri), laborar.

yusta just, equitable, rightful, fair, justifiable (cf. yurizita, equitatoza, justa); 
yust(ul)o a just act; yusteso (moral) justness, justice, fairness, uprightness, integrity (cf. equitato, yuro); 
yustigar to make just (cf. justifikar); esez yusta e ne timez be just and fear not. 
Def.: Konforma a personala justeso, a la yuro, a la raciono.

zono (geog., geom.) zone; (for body) girdle, belt, sash, waist-band (cf. 
tayo); zonizar to girdle, girt; inclose in a z.; -o torida: torrid z.; 
zono militala military z.; zonokateno chatelaine; espado zono sword-belt; 
kordo zonizis lumbo (od, tayo): his loins were girt with a cord.
